Nehawu President Mzwandile Makwayiba also called on the African National Congress to stop imposing leaders on the people if it wants to win back the metros it has lost. JOHANNESBURG The National Health Education &amp; Allied Workers Union s (Nehawu) President Mzwandile Makwayiba is warning that constitutional democracy is problematic and says it s simply not working for the country. Because comrades, when 62% majority in Parliament decide, when few individuals are not happy, they go to court and six men and women they decide on behalf of the 62%. That s my problem. The union is holding its elective conference in Boksburg on Monday.Makwayiba also called on the African National Congress to stop imposing leaders on the people if it wants to win back lower metros. That we be able to take the mass part of Johannesburg under Mashaba, that we must take the mass part of Tshwane away from DA. But we must tell the African National Congress: Stop imposing candidates to the people. Deputy President Cyril Ramaphos a arrived to a warm welcome earlier.He's started his address to the conference.#Nehawu Ramaphosa has arrived. CM pic.twitter.com/ZlGezIPg4g(Edited by Zinhle Nkosi)